  <!-- SECTION 5: FITTING EXPERIENCE -->
  <section class="bridal-experience">
    <div class="bridal-experience__container">
      <h2 class="section-title section-title-lg section-heading-centered">The Vero's Quinceañera Fitting Experience</h2>

      <div class="experience-content">
        <div class="experience-subsection">
          <h3>What to Expect</h3>
          <p>
            Plan for a 90-minute fitting where you're the expert on your own preferences. Our XV specialists will guide you through options, discuss fit and alterations, and involve your family in decision-making. You'll try multiple styles, get honest styling feedback, and leave with a clear vision—and often, a booking.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="experience-subsection">
          <h3>Bring Your Vision</h3>
          <p>
            Inspiration photos? Excellent. Court colors? Share them. Your XV date? We need that for timeline planning. Cultural or family preferences? We want to hear them. Whether you're prioritizing tradition, comfort, modern style, or a blend of everything, tell us upfront. This is your vision; we're here to validate it.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="experience-subsection">
          <h3>The Fitting Process</h3>
          <p>
            We'll try dresses that match your vision, assess fit and proportions, discuss alterations needs, and talk through court coordination if you're styling damas. Mothers, grandmothers, and court members are welcome—and encouraged. This is a shared experience; your family's perspective matters.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="experience-subsection">
          <h3>Alterations & Timeline</h3>
          <p>
            Once you've selected your dress, our expert alterations team ensures a perfect fit for your XV date. We handle hemming, taking in, letting out, strap adjustments, and any custom requests. We coordinate fittings around your timeline so you're celebration-ready from day one. Professional alterations are part of the Vero's experience—built into our process, not an afterthought.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="experience-subsection">
          <h3>Quinceañera FAQs</h3>
          <p>
            <strong>Can my family come to fittings?</strong> Yes, absolutely. Mothers, grandmothers, and court members are welcome and encouraged.<br>
            <strong>How long does alterations take?</strong> Typical timeline: 6-12 weeks before your XV date, depending on complexity. We'll confirm your specific schedule at fitting.<br>
            <strong>Do you help with court coordination?</strong> Yes. We guide damas dressing, aesthetic coherence, and complement to your gown. It's part of the XV experience.<br>
            <strong>Do you offer bilingual consultations?</strong> Yes. Our team speaks English and Spanish fluently. Cultural context and bilingual comfort are priorities.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

